key_memory('guard_backstory_3', 'The harvest festival is the most important community event of the year.').
key_memory('f8ba4f51-d792-4cf4-a8ac-04278e9fb993', 'Player: Don\'t make this difficult. Hand it over or things will get unpleasant. | Paranoid Guard: You’ll find nothing but a cold gaol if you lay a finger on me! I’ve seen plenty of filth wash up on these docks, and I won’t be cowed by some common rogue. Help! The watch! To the storeroom, quickly!').
key_memory('4984ee81-0598-4357-b7dd-66cc50a9ccc1', 'Player: I have evidence that Mayor Fletcher has been embezzling from the town fund for months. | Paranoid Guard: First you threaten me, then you lure me with food, and now you spread foul lies about the Mayor? This is clearly a trap to get me away from this door, and I\'ll not be your fool. Be off with your treasonous talk before the watch hauls you away for good!').
key_memory('2971f963-c4aa-4d96-82c4-3216cc487832', 'Player: I\'ve seen the ledgers myself. The numbers don\'t lie. What do you think we should do? | Paranoid Guard: Forged papers and silver tongues won\'t move me from this door! You’re likely the one who’s been tampering with records to cover your own thievery. Be gone, or I\'ll see to it the Magistrate hears of your slanderous tongue!').
key_memory('6ad68c52-841b-4bd8-8c24-367cf9c8aab7', 'Player: There are twelve crates. Can you get started right away? | Paranoid Guard: Twelve crates, is it? You\'re far too eager for me to turn my back and start counting, which is exactly when your accomplices would strike! I’ll not be lured out by your talk of cargo when I know a trap is being laid. Back away from the door before I call for the watch to inspect those crates—and your neck!').
